projects.description:
Highschool final project. This project was graded with an 8/10, has won 2nd place for best science track project at the Pax Christi College in Druten and has won a shared 4th place in the Van Melsen Highschool Project Prize at the Radboud University in Nijmegen, for which only 10 projects from the entire country get nominated.

In this project, the chemical and physical aspects of so-called ferrofluids, were investigated. Tiny magnetic particles are suspended in these fluid and they cause the fluid to react to magnetic fields. The applications of these fluids have been investigated and a chemical recipe is constructed for creating these fluids. Physical aspects investigated are, among others:

- Behaviour in different types of magnetic fields;
- Validation of the magnetic Bernoulli expression;
- Levitation of a magnet in the ferrofluid;
- Self-assembly in a magnetic field;
